description: Main table for delivery-level data with comprehensive metrics
notes: Primary key is delivery_id. Always filter on is_filtered_core=TRUE to remove test data.

description: Store-level table for New Verticals (non-restaurant) stores
notes: New Verticals includes all stores that are not restaurants (grocery, convenience, Dashmart aka 1P convenience, alcohol, retail, etc.). Verticals are defined in vertical_name or cng_business_line. Stores refer to individual locations.

description: Financial source of truth for gov, variable profit, etc.
notes: May be duplicative to dimension_deliveries, but preferred for 100% correct financial data. For adhocs/directional reads or when performance is a blocker, can skip this join and use dimension_deliveries directly.

description: Item-level details for non-restaurant orders in New Verticals
notes: Contains detailed information about individual items in non-restaurant orders (New Verticals orders including grocery, convenience, DashMart, alcohol, and retail). 'non-rx' refers to non-restaurant, not prescriptions.

description: Comprehensive consumer growth state accounting for New Verticals
notes: Provides detailed consumer growth metrics for New Verticals including acquisition, retention, and churn data.

description: New Verticals customer growth metrics and states
notes: Contains customer growth metrics specific to New Verticals business lines, tracking user states across the customer lifecycle.

description: Notification reach data for consumer segments
notes: Contains data about which consumers were targeted and reached by notifications.
Tracks how consumers engage with notifications, including opens, clicks, and conversion metrics.

description: Store impression data for consumer interactions
notes: Records when stores are shown to consumers in the app, important for conversion tracking.

description: Primary table for experiment analysis results
notes: Contains experiment metadata and high-level analysis results.

description: Detailed metric results for experiment analysis
notes: Contains detailed metrics and statistical analysis for experiments.

description: Detailed dimension breakdowns for experiment metrics
notes: Contains granular dimension-level breakdowns of experiment metrics.
Links experiment metrics to their dimension breakdowns.
Contains deduplicated data about user exposures to experiments.
Personal schema table containing deduplicated store impression data for analysis.
Ad-hoc table for tracking notification channels and performance for New Verticals. Only use for specific notification channel analyses.

description: Financial table for delivery allocation with marginal variable profit metrics
notes: Contains marginal_variable_profit which is a near true-to-transaction version of variable_profit, excluding P2C costs and peanutbuttered costs
